This is how I see the MCU playing out as simplified as possible.
Phase 4 is basically playing out like Phase 1.
We'll start with chaos and as the phases progress, the dots will connect.

Think about what the last movie in the phase is and consider potential post-credits.

- Kevin Feige said we'll see Kang in Ant-Man, that is most likely.
- I think potentially the main villain of Ant-Man though, could be M.O.D.O.K and we'll see Kang more as a subplot or post-credit scene. (Kang's version of Thanos' "Fine I'll do it myself")

- Doctor Doom may just continue what Kang started and once the "incursions" are wild enough, he'll set up the concept of the battle world where there are hundreds of variants of each hero.
- Not sure what direction they'll take that in the MCU but it seems likely.

- Kang will probably be crucial in setting up the beginning of Secret Wars
- However, the avengers (old + young) might defeat him
- Meanwhile, the Fantastic 4 are probably dealing with Doctor Doom (by their 2nd movie maybe)
